In [[telecommunication]], the term '''record communication''' has the following meanings: 

<b>1.</b>  A telecommunications process that produces an electronic [[message]] that is transmitted, received, stored or archived, and may be retrieved. 

<b>2.</b>  A telecommunications process, that produces a [[hard copy]] [[record]] of the [[transmission]], such as a [[teletypewriter]] printout or a [[facsimile]] printout.

Source: from [[Federal Standard 1037C]] and from [[MIL-STD-188]]